  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6593 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6500 (-4.8B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+2.0B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but primed for violent moves in either direction. The massive negative GEX wall at 6500 creates a danger zone where any move lower will force dealers to sell aggressively into weakness, while a break above the 6605 positive gamma ceiling will trigger systematic selling that could cap upside momentum. The \"gex_surge\" event combined with -71.9% GEX deterioration signals dealers are rapidly accumulating short gamma positions, setting up for explosive trending moves once we break key levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent moves if we break below 6500 or above 6605, with chop in between.",
